title: 820-00045 from hell
message:
Good evening people, 
I have received not 1 but 2 820-00045 with the same issue but not with the same problem.

One of them power cycles, and the other one does nothing.
Pp5v_s5  goes up and down on the one that cycles, and on the other one is 0v.
no shorts on any rail.
Any suggestions?

title: 820-00045 from hell
message: Probably dead CPU like every other 12" MacBook. If customer needs data, reflow/reball CPU is a good option. If no data needed, then trash.

title: 820-00045 from hell
message:
Probably hopeless project.
Check for short on big coils, try to start in SMC bypass mode.
Compare diode mode readings on the power rails between both boards.
